Honestly I think what #8217;s important to take from this whole situation is that John is a person. Fallible and imperfect and human above all else. I think that realization is really where all the panic is coming from. This fan base in particular really does engage in the outright hero worship of JD and honestly myself included for a while (they #8217;ve been my favorite band since I was 11 though so it #8217;s hard to avoid that kind of thinking when you #8217;re young). This whole fiasco forces you to realize that no he really isn #8217;t your spiritual father figure come to deliver you from your trauma he #8217;s just...a guy. Who fucks up. Do I think what John did was inappropriate? Yeah, I don #8217;t think the artist-fan power dynamic can responsibly allow for that kind of console-me-I-need-you intimacy. I think it was emotionally immature at best. But do I think he #8217;s an abuser? Absolutely not. He #8217;s just an obviously mentally ill guy who I think genuinely tries his best to do good. I don #8217;t think there was any malicious calculated intent like op implied. I just believe that there was an irresponsible lack of boundaries from JD but really, nothing he did is that horrific it #8217;s just the realization that he #8217;s not perfect that #8217;s earth shattering for some. I hope both John and the op find peace with this situation.

Really well said. It #8217;s refreshing to have a nuanced take instead of the dueling John-did-nothing-wrong and john-is-a-monster takes I #8217;ve seen online. I can only hope this all works out well for everyone involved.
